We have a bunch of Pride activities planned for June, including performances by drag queens from CANADA'S DRAG RACE!! &#128578; Plus, the date for the Out on Screen film event is confirmed!
Check out the calendar below!

Pride was held on September 19, 2015 and featured the following events&#58;

Pride Festival&#58; Held at Riverside Veterans' Memorial Park from 12 p.m. to 5 p.m. The festival featured live and recorded performances from Michael Shane, Netty Mac and rock band Gas City Shocker.
16+ Pride After Dark AfterParty&#58; Held at Medicine Hat Legion Cortona Room starting at 8 p.m. with performances by DJ Dopamine, Argintina, Elektra Kute, Violet Viofara and more.

Medicine Hat College's Pride Week ran from September 16-19, 2019 and featured the following events&#58;

September 16, 2019&#58; Pride week kicked off with a flag raising ceremony at MHC Main Entrance at 12PM
September 16-19, 2019&#58; Information Fair and Fun &amp; Gaymes in The Den from 11AM-1PM

The Pride Association of Southeast Alberta held two Pride events on June 28, 2021 in acknowledgement of Pride Month and the anniversary of the Stonewall Inn Riots. These events included the following&#58;

June 28, 2021&#58; Queer Cookout at Kin Coulee Park at 6 p.m.
June 28, 2021&#58; Lights for a Cause&#58; Lighting up the Saamis Teepee in rainbow colours in honour of Pride Month and the anniversary of the Stonewall Inn riots at dusk

The Pride Association of Southeast Alberta, in partnership with Spectrum Festival, held two Pride events in June 2022&#58;

June 3&#58; White Party at Whiskey Creek beginning at 9pm ($10 Cover). Featuring The Dalai Jamma, Ohmzone and Crook3dmindz
June 4, 2022&#58; Free Spectrum Style Pride at Kin Coulee Park from 10AM - 3&#58;30 PM. Amateur Drag Show from 10AM - 10&#58;40am with featuring Roxxie Cotton, Jazmyn Jewelz and Jamie Slayer Moore and a performance by Old Soul Rebel from 2PM – 3&#58;30 PM. Event held in collaboration with Southern Alberta Pop Up Parks
